%% Diagram: DNS cache layers and time-to-evict after a backend crash
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant App as Client App
    participant RT as Language Runtime Cache
    participant OS as OS Stub Resolver
    participant Up as Recursive Resolver
    participant Reg as Authoritative DNS / Registry
    participant B as Backend A

    Note over Reg: TTL = 30s
    App->>RT: resolve service.local
    RT->>OS: lookup
    OS->>Up: query
    Up->>Reg: query
    Reg-->>Up: A 10.0.0.5 TTL=30
    Up-->>OS: cached
    OS-->>RT: cached
    RT-->>App: 10.0.0.5

    App->>B: HTTP request
    B-->>App: 200 OK

    Note over B: Backend A crashes at T=5s
    Reg->>Reg: Health check fails, A removed at T=15s

    loop Until each cache layer expires
        App->>B: more requests on existing connection
        B--xApp: connection refused / timeout
    end

    Note over App,Reg: Worst-case time-to-evict =\nrecursive_TTL + os_ttl + runtime_ttl + connection_lifetime
